The paper discusses nearest neighbor search, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision, recommendation systems, and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses loss functions and similarity preservation, which are common topics in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The paper also mentions multi-modal deep hashing methods, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses public datasets and performance measurement, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases).
